  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Recent result of BICEP2, revealing a larger value of tensor to scalar ratio ($r$), has opened up new investigations of the inflationary models to fit the experimental data. Though the experiment needs to reconfirm the results, specifically the consistency between Planck and BICEP2 has to be achieved, the combined analysis of Planck and BICEP2 B modes including the dust polarization uncertainty, on the other hand, brings down the upper limit on $r$. In this note, we reexamine the Chromo Natural Inflation model and its generalization in view of such observational data. We find that the parameter space of the model admits a large value of $r$ as well as other cosmological observables consistent with data.</subfield>
